Windwalker Monk Mythic+ Guide

11.1 - Undermine(d)

Last Updated:February 26, 2025|Changelog|FAQ

Welcome to the Windwalker Monk Mythic+ guide for the World of Warcraft patch 11.1! This guide covers everything you need to know to understand your character! Are you starting out and leveling up from 70? Check out the leveling guide!

Hero Talents

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk
  • Conduit of the Celestials     does outperform
    Shado-Pan     in the raid currently, but you can play both hero talents in dungeons now.
Shado-Pan
Conduit of the Celestials
  • Every 240 Energy you spent while in combat, you unleash
    Flurry Strikes    , which makes it vital to not overcap Energy.
  • Efficient Training
    • Spending 50 Energy spent reduces the cooldown of
      Storm, Earth, and Fire       by 1 second.
  • Wisdom of the Wall
    • Every time
      Flurry Strikes       proccs with 10 stacks(it is pretty much guaranteed) you gain one of the four buffs.
    • It is possible to have multiple buffs at the same time.
  • Shado-Pan     Choice Nodes are:
    • Pride of Pandaria
    • Protect and Serve
      • Protect and Serve         provides a decent chunk of healing combined with
        Vivacious Vivification        .
    • Whirling Steel
  • Gain access to
    Celestial Conduit     a powerful 90 second cooldown that lines up with
    Storm, Earth, and Fire    .
  • Heart of the Jade Serpent
    • Your
      Strike of the Windlord       grants you 75% cooldown reduction on
      Rising Sun Kick      ,
      Fists of Fury      ,
      Strike of the Windlord       and
      Whirling Dragon Punch      .
    • While it is up your
      Fists of Fury       channel time is reduced by 50%.
  • Unity Within
    • After finishing your
      Celestial Conduit       you spawn all Celestials.
    • It is also possible to finish the channel early to spawn them faster.

Talents

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk
Shado-Pan
Conduit of the Celestials

When to use this Spec

It is your choice whether you play

Shado-Pan or
Celestial Conduit in dungeons. Although for some dungeons some minor talents in the class tree will change for some different utility options. To make your life easier, dungeon-specific talent loadouts are available in the Dungeons section.

Gameplay Altering Talents

Discover all talents that significantly alter your gameplay within the Spec and Class Talent trees. This section gives a concise overview of these talents and their applications but for a more detailed look check out the Rotation and Deep Dive sections below.

Spec Tree

  • Revolving Whirl
    • Whirling Dragon Punch       grants you a guaranteed
      Dance of Chi-Ji       proc.
  • Dance of Chi-Ji
    • Always prioritize using
      Spinning Crane Kick       when it procs before casting
      Blackout Kick      .
    • You can have 2 stacks of
      Dance of Chi-Ji       now.
  • Ordered Elements
    • Your
      Rising Sun Kick       cooldown resets after activating
      Storm, Earth, and Fire       so you want to press
      Rising Sun Kick       before
      Storm, Earth, and Fire      .
    • Your Chi spenders cost 1 less Chi during
      Storm, Earth, and Fire      .
  • Last Emperor's Capacitor
    • Your Chi spenders grant you a stack of
      Last Emperor's Capacitor       up to 20.
  • Power of the Thunder King
    • Crackling Jade Lightning       cleaves 4 additional targets with 80% effectiveness and the casttime is reduced by 50%.
  • Spiritual Focus
    • Chi you spend reduces the cooldown of
      Storm, Earth, and Fire      .
  • Sequenced Strikes
    • Consuming a
      Dance of Chi-Ji       proc grants you a
      Blackout Kick!       proc.
  • Energy Burst
    • You gain 1 Chi after using a
      Blackout Kick!       proc.

Class Tree

  • Summon White Tiger Statue
    • Using
      Invoke Xuen, the White Tiger       spawns a statue at your location that damages nearby enemies.
  • Fatal Touch
    • Prioritize using
      Touch of Death       whenever possible as you gain a 5% damage buff.

Hero Talents

  • Pride of Pandaria
    • Your default pick since
      High Impact       is weaker.
  • Protect and Serve
    • Provides a decent chunk of heal especially combined with
      Vivacious Vivification      .
  • Whirling Steel

Rotation

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk

Tier Set

  • 2-Set: Your spells and abilities have a chance to activate
    Winning Streak!     increasing the damage of your next
    Rising Sun Kick     and
    Spinning Crane Kick     by 3% stacking up to 10 times.
    Rising Sun Kick     and
    Spinning Crane Kick     have a 15% chance to remove
    Winning Streak!    .
  • 4-Set:
    Fists of Fury     applies 1 stack of
    Winning Streak!     when cast and when finished channeling completely. The damage of your next
    Fists of Fury     is increased by 8% per stack when
    Winning Streak!     is removed. Your
    Winning Streak!     is always removed once it reaches max stacks.

Single-Target

Shado-Pan

Opener

  • Your goal is to cast as many Chi spenders as possible in your
    Storm, Earth, and Fire     window while also keeping relevant abilities on cooldown.

Priority List

This is a general priority you aim to maintain throughout the fight.

  1. Touch of Death     if possible.
  2. Rising Sun Kick     when buffed by
    Xuen's Battlegear    .
  3. Tiger Palm     if below 5 Chi and close to capping Energy.
  4. Strike of the Windlord    .
  5. Whirling Dragon Punch     if possible.
  6. Rising Sun Kick    .
  7. Tiger Palm     if you are capping energy.
  8. Fists of Fury    .
  9. Blackout Kick     to not overcap on stacks of
    Teachings of the Monastery    .
  10. Spinning Crane Kick     with
    Dance of Chi-Ji    .
  11. Tiger Palm     it is a gain to overcap Chi, to spend energy.
  12. Jadefire Stomp     if talented paired with either
    Singularly Focused Jade     or
    Jadefire Harmony    .
  13. Blackout Kick    .
  14. Chi Burst    .

AoE

Shado-Pan

Opener

  • Below you can see one variation of the multi-target opener rotation using the
    Shado-Pan    .

Priority List

  1. Tiger Palm     if below 5 Chi and close to capping Energy.
  2. Touch of Death     if possible.
  3. Spinning Crane Kick     with
    Dance of Chi-Ji     with 2 stacks to not overcap.
  4. Whirling Dragon Punch    .
  5. Strike of the Windlord    .
  6. Crackling Jade Lightning     if you are overcapping Last Emperor's Capacitor with Power of the Thunder King talented.
  7. Fists of Fury    .
  8. Rising Sun Kick     for
    Whirling Dragon Punch     if possible.
  9. Jadefire Stomp     if talented paired with either
    Singularly Focused Jade     or
    Jadefire Harmony    .
  10. Spinning Crane Kick    .
  11. Blackout Kick     to not overcap on stacks of
    Teachings of the Monastery    .
  12. Chi Burst     if talented.

Deep dive

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk

Mastery

  • It is very important to never break your
    Mastery: Combo Strikes     or
    Hit Combo    .
  • During downtime you can use
    Spinning Crane Kick     to keep up your
    Hit Combo    .
  • If the boss is immune to damage you can also use
    Crackling Jade Lightning     to keep it up.

Touch of Karma

  • To maximize your damage output you want to press
    Touch of Karma     on every damage event possible in the fight.
  • You can increase the absorbed amount of your
    Touch of Karma     damage by using
    Fortifying Brew     beforehand to increase your maximum health.
  • When grouped with a Warrior, you can ask them to press
    Rallying Cry     if it is not needed as a cooldown to get even more health before using
    Touch of Karma    .

Touch of Death

  • As a Windwalker Monk it is very important for you to snipe any low health add with
    Touch of Death    .
  • You gain
    Fatal Touch     after executing
    Touch of Death    .

Storm, Earth, and Fire

  • Your clones prioritize hitting targets that have no
    Mark of the Crane     on them as their mimicked abilities apply it.
  • Only do this if you are confident that you can keep up 5
    Mark of the Crane     stacks and you know that you are missing out on potential cleave value.
    • You can press
      Storm, Earth, and Fire       again to fixate your clones on a target after getting 5
      Mark of the Crane       stacks. It is especially good if your clones hit targets far away from the rest of the enemies that you would otherwise not be able to spread
      Mark of the Crane       to.
    • It is a must to fixate your clones again after your fixate target dies.
      • They will do nothing if you don't do it.
    • It is extremely important to fixate your clones otherwise you could miss out on potential cleave from
      Whirling Dragon Punch      ,
      Fists of Fury      , and
      Spinning Crane Kick      .

Energy usage with
Shado-Pan

  • It is extremely vital to not overcap Energy to use
    Flurry Strikes     at your maximum potential.
  • Especially during downtime make use of
    Vivify     to not overcap Energy, so you can reduce the cooldown of
    Storm, Earth, and Fire    .
    • Important to note that the Energy used from
      Vivify       does not count towards
      Flurry Strikes      .
  • During downtime you can use
    Paralysis     and
    Crackling Jade Lightning     to spend Energy for
    Flurry Strikes    .
    • This only works with a target that you can hit.

Two handed weapon versus one hand weapons

  • With the increased item level of the new gear using a two hand weapon does outshine one hand weapons especially in AoE scenarios, one handers overtake them in single target with the new very rare weapons only.

Boss Tips

Brew Master Aldryr

  • Use
    Touch of Karma    ,
    Fortifying Brew     or
    Diffuse Magic     on
    Throw Cinderbrew    .
  • Put down a
    Transcendence     on the boss for the
    Happy Hour    , you can give one of your partymembers with less mobility
    Tiger's Lust     to get through the intermission faster.
    • Watch out for your health during this intermission, you can easily outrange your healer during this.

I'pa

  • Pop
    Touch of Karma    ,
    Fortifying Brew     or
    Diffuse Magic     on
    Burning Fermentation    .
  • It is important to never let the Brew Drops reach I'pa.
    • Crowd control the Brew Drops with
      Leg Sweep      ,
      Ring of Peace       and
      Flying Serpent Kick       if necessary.

Benk Buzzbee

  • Keep your
    Touch of Karma    ,
    Fortifying Brew     incase you get a lot of
    Shredding Sting     stacks.
  • Help the Tank out with
    Ring of Peace     to not let the Ravenous Cinderbees soak the
    Honey Marinade     on the floor.
  • It is a good idea to use
    Diffuse Magic     on
    Fluttering Wing     as it is the only magic damage event in the fight.
  • Once you kill a Ravenous Cinderbee you can mount up on them
    Tamed    , and kill the
    Snack Time    .

Goldie Baronbottom

  • Avoid the front of the boss at all costs to dodge the
    Cash Cannon    .
  • Keep the room clean from
    Cinder-BOOM!     and burn the barrels with
    Burning Ricochet    .
    • Be aware that clearing up multiple of the barrels does apply a deadly dot on all players
      Cindering Wounds      .
  • The boss casts
    Let It Hail!     upon reaching 100 Energy, use
    Touch of Karma    ,
    Fortifying Brew     or
    Diffuse Magic     on it.
    • Keep in mind that all the Cinderbrew Bombs explode and if you have
      Cinder-BOOM!       on the ground you want to press even more personals and a healthpotion or healthstone.

Trash Tips

  • Single targeting the Yes Man is important, as they full heal themselves as one of them dies with
    Field Promotion    .
  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Boiling Flames       from Venture Co. Pyromaniac.
    • Free Samples?       from Taste Tester.
    • Rejuvenating Honey       from Flavor Scientist.
    • Bee-stial Wrath       from Bee Wrangler.
    • Honey Volley       from Royal Jelly Purveyor.
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Throw Chair       from Hired Muscle.
      • Inflicts physical damage to a random player. Make sure you are always full health whenever getting targeted by this spell. Always be ready to press a strong defensive like
        Touch of Karma         or
        Fortifying Brew        .
    • Reckless Delivery       from Careless Hopgoblin
      • Targets a player and the Careless Hopgoblin charges towards the direction of the player, make sure to bait it close to the trash pack that you are fighting so he does not move very far away.
    • Failed Batch       from Flavor Scientist.
      • Summons a Failed Batch that starts a 10 second cast which will inflict AoE fire damage to all players upon succeeding. Swap to it as soon as it spawns to kill it as quickly as possible.
    • Swarming Surprise       from Venture Co. Honey Harvester.
      • An AoE cast that ramps in damage done per cast.
  • Dangerous debuffs to be wary of:
    • Erupting Inferno       from Venture Co. Pyromaniac.
    • Mean Mug       from Venture Co. Patron.
      • It does only apply on the tank but you can help the tank reset his stacks with
        Ring of Peace         and
        Leg Sweep        .
    • Applies a Magic debuff to a random player, inflicting heavy fire damage. Be careful if you are not dispelled and use
      Diffuse Magic      .
    • Shredding Sting       from Worker Bee.
      • A stacking Bleed that is applied to random players. Use a
        Touch of Karma         or
        Fortifying Brew         if you get multiple of those stacks.

Boss Tips

Ol' Waxbeard

  • Be aware of the Menial Laborers when targeted by
    Luring Candleflame    .
    • Use
      Leg Sweep       and
      Ring of Peace       to keep the Menial Laborers in melee.
  • It is your highest priority to kill the Dynamite Mine Card as it spawns.
  • Bait
    Reckless Charge     close to a wall so the boss does not move too far away.

Blazikon

  • Your goal is to ignite as many candles as possible with
    Wicklighter Barrage    , to decrease the damage from
    Enkindling Inferno    .
  • Hit atleast 1 candle with
    Extinguishing Gust     to gurantee a safe spot for
    Incite Flames    .
    • Extinguishing Gust       is a very fast projectile from the boss make sure to not get hit by it.

The Candle King

  • Interrupt
    Paranoid Mind    .
    • you can rotate interrupts with melee two interrupts.
  • Hide behind a Wax Statue after targeted the The Candle King by
    Darkflame Pickaxe    .
  • Rotate
    Diffuse Magic    ,
    Touch of Karma     or
    Fortifying Brew     on
    Throw Darkflame    .
    • You want to melt down the Wax Statues with it.

The Darkness

  • The Darkness casts
    Call Darkspawn     interrupt it.
  • Keep the Candlelight safe from the
    Umbral Slash    .

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Wicklighter Bolt       from Royal Wicklighter.
    • Mole Frenzy       from Lowly Moleherd.
    • Explosive Flame       from Blazing Fiend.
    • Flaming Tether       from Sootsnout.
    • Drain Light       from Shuffling Horror.
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Throw Rock       from Lowly Moleherd.
    • Pay attention to your health whenever you are spam targeted by this spell, especially if Lowly Moleherd is
      Panicked!      .
    • One-Hand Headlock       from Torchsnarl.
      • Ceaseless Flame         is cast by Sootsnout on the person targeted by
        One-Hand Headlock        , use
        Diffuse Magic        ,
        Touch of Karma         or
        Fortifying Brew         on it.
    • Wild Wallop       from Rank Overseer.
      • This ability knocks every target not differentiating from enemies or allies.
  • Dangerous debuffs to be wary of:
    • Flashpoint       from Royal Wicklighter.
    • Applies a Magic debuff to a random player, inflicting heavy fire damage. Be careful if you are not dispelled and use a defensive.
    • Explosive Flame       from Blazing Fiend.
      • Be careful if you get too many stacks of this debuff and press a defensive if the cast goes through multiple times.

Boss Tips

Tussle Tonks

  • Put down a
    Transcendence     incase you get targeted by
    Foe Flipper     to maximize uptime on the bosses.
  • Use
    Touch of Karma     or
    Fortifying Brew     during
    Ground Pound    .
  • To maximize cleave damage on both bosses, you use cooldowns when the boss is not buffed by
    Platinum Plating    .
  • Kill the Platinum Pummeler and Gnomercy 4.U. at the same time to avoid
    Electrical Storm    .

K.U-J.O

  • During
    Explosive Leap     avoid hitting the
    Junk Bomb    .
    • Rotate
      Diffuse Magic      ,
      Touch of Karma       or
      Fortifying Brew       on
      Explosive Leap      .
  • While K.U-J.O casts
    Venting Flames     you can keep hitting the boss as long as you are affected by
    Hiding Behind Junk    .

Machinist's Garden

  • Always watch your surroundings to easily dodge
    Self-Trimming Hedge    .
  • Rotate
    Diffuse Magic    ,
    Touch of Karma     or
    Fortifying Brew     when targeted by
    Blossom Blast    .
    • The Inconspicuous Plant can be affected by
      Leg Sweep      .
  • During
    "Hidden" Flame Cannon     look at the middle of the room and you see the direction which the
    "Hidden" Flame Cannon     turn.

King Mechagon

  • Throughout the fight the
    Plasma Orb     adjust their positioning around different players on
    Recalibrate    .
    • Watch the arrows closely to avoid getting clipped by it.
  • Rotate
    Diffuse Magic    ,
    Touch of Karma     or
    Fortifying Brew     when targeted by
    Mega-Zap    .
  • During
    Take Off!     the
    Cutting Beam     does not hit you as long as you stay on max melee range.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Detonate       from Bomb Tonk.
    • Giga-Wallop       from Mechagon Tinkerer.
    • Tune Up       from Mechagon Mechanic.
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Mega Drill       from Waste Processing Unit.
      • Inflicts nature damage to all players. Stack up with the group and use defensives.
    • Short Out       from Defense Bot Mk III.
      • Short channeled cast that inflicts nature damage to all players. Use a defensive whenever it happens.
    • Shield Generator       from Workshop Defender.
      • The
        Shield Generator         decreases the damage everyone takes whether its friend or foe, ensure you are standing in it to decrease your damage intake.
        • Use
          Ring of Peace           to keep the mobs outside the
          Shield Generator          .
  • Dangerous debuffs to be wary of:
    • Fiery Jaws       from Junkyard D.0.G.
    • Applies a Magic debuff to a random player, inflicting heavy fire damage. Be careful if you are not dispelled and use a defensive.
    • Arcing Zap       from Defense Bot Mk I and Defense Bot Mk III.
      • Applies a Magic debuff to a random player, inflicting nature damage. Be careful if you are not dispelled and use a defensive.
        • Diffuse Magic           deals massive amount of damage to the enemy.

Boss Tips

Big M.O.M.M.A

  • One of the Darkfuse Mechadrone casts
    Maximum Distortion     always interrupt it.
  • Disengage from the boss after beeing targeted by
    Sonic Boom     to avoid getting hit by it.
  • During the first phase always hit the Darkfuse Mechadrones as it triggers the second phase after all of them are dead.
    • If you take too long to kill the Darkfuse Mechadrones Big M.O.M.M.A casts
      Kill-o-Block Barrier       .
  • Phase 2 is a burn phase, hold your cooldowns for
    Jumpstart     it is a 200% damage increase.
    • Use your
      Touch of Karma       to maximize damage during it.

Demolition Duo

  • Kill both bosses in a similar time to avoid
    Divided Duo    .
  • Diffuse
    Big Bada BOOM!     with
    Barreling Charge     and
    Kinetic Explosive Gel    .
    • You can dispel yourself from
      Kinetic Explosive Gel       with
      Diffuse Magic      , make sure you are close to a bomb to diffuse them.
  • In general it is a good idea to use
    Touch of Karma     and
    Fortifying Brew     on
    Kinetic Explosive Gel    .

Swampface

  • Razorchoke Vines     links you together with another player(it cannot be the tank unless people are dead), and you have to move together.
    • Usually there is a set rule to always dodge mechanics left or right depending on agreement with the group.
  • It is a good idea to use
    Diffuse Magic    ,
    Touch of Karma     or wow-trait id=124968]Fortifying Brew[/wow-trait] on
    Awaken the Swamp     incase you get hit by
    Rushing Tide    .

Geezle Gigazap

  • During
    Turbo Charge     you should use a strong personal like
    Fortifying Brew    .
    • Be careful with
      Whirling Dragon Punch       to not get hit by
      Turbo Bolt       .
  • Use
    Diffuse Magic     or
    Touch of Karma     when targeted by
    Gigazap    .
  • Kite the
    Leaping Sparks     towards
    Dam Water     on the ground.
    • You can touch the water as long as the spark did not reach it yet.

Trash Tips

  • Important abilities to interrupt in this dungeon are:
    • Trickshot       from Mechadrone Sniper.
    • Surveying Beam       from Venture Co. Surveyor.
    • Bloodthirsty Cackle       from Darkfuse Hyena.
    • Blood Blast       from Darkfuse Bloodwarper.
    • Restorative Algae       from Disturbed Kelp.
      • You can stun these as well but they will recast untill interrupted.
    • Harpoon       from Venture Co. Diver.
    • Lightning Bolt       from Venture Co. Electrician.
  • Pay extra attention to these casts:
    • Wind Up       from Loaderbot.
      • Fixates a random player, inflicting physical damage to players within 3.5 yards for 6 seconds. Don't be in melee or close to the mob whenever it happens.
    • Shreddation       from Shreddinator 3000.
      • Summons several spinning sawblades at the location of every player, inflicting physical damage every 0.3 seconds to players within the effect. This damage increases with consecutive hits. Damage can be fully avoided by prerunning out of it before the cast finishes.
      • Flamethrower         from Shreddinator 3000.
        • It can be very spicy to dodge the
          Shreddation           and the
          Flamethrower           at the same time, in worst case scenario disengage from melee.
      • Rapid Construction         from Venture Co. Architect.
        • While the Scaffolding is up, the Venture Co. Architect is buffed by
          High Ground          .
          • Focus the Scaffolding to remove
            High Ground             as fast as possible.
  • Dangerous debuffs to be wary of:
    • Overcharge       from Venture Co. Electrician.
      • Applies a Magic debuff to a random player, inflicting nature damage and stuns if the effect persists without being dispelled.

Boss Tips

Captain Dailcry

  • Depending on your route the either Elaena Emberlanz, Sergeant Shaynemail or Taener Duelmal is up.
    • Interrupt
      Repentance       from Elaena Emberlanz.
    • Sergeant Shaynemail puts a nasty bleed
      Lunging Strike      .
      • Use
        Touch of Karma         or
        Fortifying Brew         for it.
    • Taener Duelmal casts
      Cinderblast       and
      Fireball      .
      • One person in the group should always hold their interrupt for
        Cinderblast        .

Stat Priority

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk

Understand your secondary stat priority and the tertiary stats needed for optimal performance during Mythic+ dungeons as a Windwalker Monk. For more detailed information, visit the Stats and Attributes guide.

Higher Item level items are better in most scenarios. For an accurate representation of what item to equip you should use Simcraft! A static "Stat Priority" is just a starting point and can easily shift depending on your individual gear.

All secondary stats are affected by diminishing returns. Click here to learn more!

Tertiary

  • Avoidance - Great stat to reduce the damage intake of "Area of Effect" abilities.
  • Leech - Provides additional healing through damage dealing. The damage of your pets does not heal you thus Leech is a great tertiary for you since most of your damage is coming from your own spells.
  • Speed - Niche tertiary that can be very useful and has been proven useful in the past. Makes playing certain mechanics a lot easier.

Races

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk

For min-maxing a Windwalker Monk in Mythic+, different racial traits can provide a tremendous benefit to your character. If this is not your top goal, picking a race that fits your style works just as well.

  • Stoneform     -- Dwarf
    • One of the most potent racials in Mythic+ currently and historically.
    • Dispels Magic and Bleed debuffs.
    • Use-cases:
      • Curse of Entropy        , Drahga Shadowburner (Grim Batol)
      • Cultivated Poisons        , Ki'katal the Harvester (Ara-Kara, City of Echoes)
      • Putrid Waters        , Viq'Goth (Siege of Boralus)
      • Venomous Spray        , Royal Venomshell (City of Threads)
  • Shadowmeld     -- Night Elf
    • Also one of the most potent racials in Mythic+ historically.
    • Run past basically any mob and then cast
      Shadowmeld       to make them reset. Even works on mobs that have stealth detection if you get enough distance before you
      Shadowmeld      .
  • Blood Fury     -- Orc
    • Strong racial for damage both because of
      Command       and
      Blood Fury       which lines up with
      Invoke Xuen, the White Tiger      .
    • 20% reduced Stun duration on you which can be useful in some Mythic+ dungeons.
  • Escape Artist     -- Gnome
    • Free yourself from roots.
  • Rocket Jump     -- Goblin
    • Do a small jump in the direction your character is facing.
    • While you're in the
      Rocket Jump       animation you are placed on a global cooldown until your character lands.
  • Berserking     -- Troll
    • Your strongest DPS racial but lines up poorly with
      Invoke Xuen, the White Tiger      .
    • Reduce the duration of movement impairing effects by 20%.

Recommendation

Dwarf and
Night Elf abilities have such a big impact on your Mythic+ experience that you need to use either of them if you're serious about pushing keys with your Windwalker Monk.

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)

Below, you see a screenshot of the author's User Interface for their Windwalker Monk, outlining which addons are used and how they are utilized in Mythic+ dungeons to make your life easier.

Addons

  • ElvUI -- Full User Interface replacement
    • A user interface designed around user-friendliness with extra features that are not included in the standard UI.
    • Alternatively, you can also use Shadowed Unit Frames (SUF) and an action bar addon of your choice or of course the stock UI.
  • LittleWigs -- Generic Boss Mod
    • BigWigs is a boss encounter add-on. It consists of many individual encounter scripts, or boss modules; mini add-ons that are designed to trigger alert messages, timer bars, sounds, and so forth, for one specific Raid encounter.
  • WeakAuras -- Jack of all trades
    • WeakAuras is a powerful and flexible framework that allows the display of highly customizable graphics on World of Warcraft's user interface to indicate buffs, debuffs, and other relevant information. This addon was created to be a lightweight replacement for Power Auras but has since introduced more functionalities while remaining efficient and easy to use.
  • Plater -- Advanced Nameplates
    • Plater is a nameplate addon with an extraordinary amount of settings, out of the box debuff tracking, threat coloring, and support for scripting similar to WeakAuras and wago.io + the WeakAuras-Companion for Mod/Script/Profile updates.
  • Details -- In-depth Damage Meter
    • Most powerful, reliable, handsome, damage meter.
  • OmniCD -- Party track addon
    • Helpful addon for Mythic+ to check the available cooldowns of your party.

Changes this Patch

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk

Patch 11.1

  • MONK
    • Paralysis now breaks based on a small damage threshold instead of any damage.
  • Windwalker
    • New Talent: Slicing Winds Envelop yourself in razor-sharp winds, then lunge forward dealing Nature damage to enemies in your path. Damage reduced beyond 5 enemies. Hold to increase lunge distance. Replaces Flying Serpent Kick.
    • Dance of the Wind has been redesigned Now reduces physical damage taken by 10% and an additional 10% every 4 seconds until you receive a physical attack.
    • Mastery: Combo Strikes effectiveness increased by 35%.
      • Developers' notes: Were increasing the value Mastery: Combo Strikes for Windwalker Monks with the goal of pushing it as a stat.
    • All damage done reduced by 2%.
    • Spinning Crane Kick damage increased by 80%.
    • Courageous Impulse now increases the damage of Blackout Kick by 350% (was 200%).
    • Shadowboxing Treads now increases the damage of Blackout Kick by 10% (was 20%).
    • Xuens Bond now reduces the cooldown of Invoke Xuen, the White Tiger by a static 30 seconds.
    • Last Emperor's Capacitor now increases the damage of Crackling Jade Lightning by 400% per stack (was 200%).
    • Power of the Thunder King now cleaves Crackling Jade Lightning at 80% effectiveness (was 100%).
    • Ordered Elements now reduces Chi costs by 1 during Storm, Earth, and Fire (was Rising Sun Kick reduces Chi costs during Storm, Earth, and Fire for 7 seconds).
    • The following talents have been removed:
      • Darting Hurricane
      • Mark of the Crane
    • Conduit of the Celestials
      • Heart of the Jade Serpent now reduces the cooldown of Flying Serpent Kick.
      • Heart of the Jade Serpent now triggers each time you cast Strike of the Windlord, but its duration has been decreased to 6 seconds.
        • Developers notes: Wed like to reduce the tracking required around Heart of the Jade Serpent as well as make it a more fundamental part of playing as a Conduit of the Celestial Monk.
      • Rising Sun Kick has been added back to Heart of the Jade Serpent.
        • Developers notes: We werent satisfied with the rotational outcome of this change and are reverting it.

Patch 11.0.05

  • MONK
    • Weapons of Order and Jadefire Stomp icons have been updated.
    • Hero Talents
      • Shado-Pan
      • Added an energy tracker aura. This aura shows the player how much energy they have spent towards their next set of Flurry Strikes.
      • Flurry Charges are no longer cancelable and no longer have a duration.
      • Flurry Strikes unleash energy trigger threshold is now 240 energy (was 300).
      • Flurry Strike damage reduced by 8%.
      • Flurry Strike Accumulator Threshold increased by 47%.
      • Wisdom of the Wall bonus effects duration reduced to 16 seconds (was 20%).
      • Against All Odds duration reduced to 5 seconds (was 6 seconds).
      • Developer's note: The goal of these changes is to allow Shado-Pan to activate Flurry Strikes more frequently and have a better understanding of when the Flurry Strikes are going to to be unleashed on their foes.
  • Windwalker
    • Blackout Kick's damage increased by 20%.
    • Flurry of Xuen damage increased by 40%.
    • Fixed an issue that caused Courageous Impulse to incorrectly buff the damage of Blackout Kick by more than intended when multiple stacks are active.
    • Fixed an issue that caused Courageous Impulse to incorrectly buff Teachings of the Monastery Blackout Kicks.

Patch 11.0.2

  • MONK
    • Healing Elixir now heals for 10% of maximum health (was 15%).

FAQ

Patch 11.1 - Undermine(d)
Windwalker Monk

Q: Why does my
Hit Combo drop?

A: You are pressing the same ability twice in a row. Common scenarios where this can happen is if your

Tiger Palm gets parried and you press two of them to gain Chi.
